dcterms:description: Meta-Learning Wizard-of-Oz is a dataset designed to help develop models capable of predicting user responses in unseen domains. This large dataset was created by crowdsourcing 37,884 goal-oriented dialogs, covering 227 tasks in 47 domains.

dcterms:description: Schema-guided dialogue has 22,825 dialogues and provides a challenging testbed for several tasks, particularly dialogue state tracking. Each schema is a set of tracking slots, allowing a single dialogue system to support many services.

dcterms:description: This dataset includes 13,215 dialogues comprising six domains, created with two distinct procedures: a Wizard of Oz approach and a self-dialogue approach where crowdsourced workers wrote the entire dialog themselves.
dcterms:title: Taskmaster

dcterms:creator: P. Budzianowski
I. Vulić
dcterms:description: Multi-Domain Wizard-of-Oz dataset contains 10,420 dialogues over seven domains, providing full database information and detailed descriptions of the data collection procedure, user goal, system act, and dialogue state labels.
dcterms:title: MWOZ

dcterms:description: Microsoft end-to-end dialogue challenge has 10,087 dialogues in three domains, including movie-ticket booking, restaurant reservation, and taxi booking, along with built-in simulators for each domain.
dcterms:title: MSR-E2E

dcterms:description: Stanford multi-domain dialogue is an in-car personal assistant dataset, comprising 3,301 dialogues across three domains: calendar scheduling, weather information retrieval, and point-of-interest navigation.
